    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Dual Stage Turbocharger Assembly -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply a light coat of clean engine oil on bolt threads and under bolt head when installing
                        used nuts and bolts.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc graphiccount="5">
            <title>Assembly of Dual Turbocharger</title>
            <figure id="f3000325" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbine housing alignment marks</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the high-pressure turbine housing on the low-pressure turbine housing and
                    loosely install the V-band clamp. Align turbine housing marks. Do not tighten V-band clamp at this
                    time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000326" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Crossover tube seal installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_145.xml" xrefid="t390000403">Turbo Crossover Tube Seal Remover /
                        Installer
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t390000403"/>
                    holding fixture into a bench vise.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install crossover tube into holding fixture and tighten clamps.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position seal onto crossover tube and drive seal into crossover tube until seal is
                    seated, using Turbo Crossover Tube Seal Remover / Installer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000327" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Small crossover seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring seal onto short end of crossover tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000328" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN15/N15012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger crossover tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crossover tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">V-band clamp</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the V-band clamp onto the crossover tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install crossover tube onto turbocharger assembly. A slight twisting motion may be
                    necessary to start the long end of tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3900004147" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN15/N15015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger oil drain tubes</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 25 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure turbocharger oil drain tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 25 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure turbocharger oil drain tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure turbocharger oil drain upper adaptor</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not pinch O-rings when installing turbocharger oil drain tubes.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on the low-pressure turbocharger oil drain tube and high-pressure
                    oil drain upper adaptor. Lubricate O-rings with clean engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the low-pressure oil drain tube and finger tighten two M8 x 25 bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the high-pressure oil drain upper adaptor and finger tighten two M8 x 25
                    bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten four M8 x 25 bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="S300GTG"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
